                    <article class="article-card grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-8 items-center mb-12">
                        <div class="lg:col-span-3">
                            <!-- Assumes main.avif is in an 'images' folder -->
                            <img src="main.avif" alt="Futuristic green cityscape" class="rounded-lg shadow-lg w-full h-auto object-cover" onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src='https://placehold.co/600x400/2d3748/ffffff?text=Derawvibes';">
                        </div>
                        <div class="lg:col-span-2">
                            <span class="article-category text-xs font-bold uppercase text-red-600">Featured Story</span>
                            <h2 class="article-title text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold my-3 leading-tight">The AI Revolution in EHS: Predictive Analytics is Changing the Game</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Forget reactive safety measures. New AI models can now predict workplace accidents before they happen...</p>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">By Devansh Singh Rawal | Published on September 28, 2025</p>
                            <a href="#" class="read-more-btn inline-block bg-black text-white font-bold py-2 px-5 rounded-md hover:bg-gray-800 transition duration-300">Read More</a>
                            <div class="article-meta hidden">
                                <img src="Passport_Photograph.jpg" alt="Author's photo" class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full mr-4 object-cover shadow-md">
                                <span class="article-author">Devansh Singh Rawal</span>
                                <span class="article-date">September 28, 2025</span>
                                <span class="article-author-img">Passport_Photograph.jpg</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="article-full-content hidden">
                                <p>For decades, Environmental, Health, and Safety (EHS) has been a field of reaction. An incident occurs, an investigation follows, and new protocols are implemented. But what if we could prevent incidents before they even happen? Welcome to the age of predictive analytics in EHS.</p>
                                <p>Artificial intelligence is no longer the stuff of science fiction; it's a powerful tool being deployed in factories, construction sites, and laboratories worldwide. By analyzing vast datasets from IoT sensors, incident reports, and even weather patterns, machine learning algorithms can identify hidden correlations and flag high-risk scenarios with astonishing accuracy.</p>
                                <blockquote>"We're moving from a culture of compliance to a culture of prediction. This is the single biggest leap forward for workplace safety in a generation."</blockquote>
                                <p>Companies at the forefront are using AI to predict equipment failures, identify at-risk employee behaviors, and model the potential impact of chemical spills. The result is not just a safer workplace, but a more efficient and resilient operation. The AI revolution isn't coming to EHS—it's already here.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </article>

